ðŸ§  Atlas Vector Search on Search Playground

In this section, you will use the Atlas Search Playground to perform a vector search using embeddings generated by OpenAI's API. If you don't have an OpenAI API key, you can use the pre-generated embeddings provided below.

What is Vector Search?â€‹

Vector search is a powerful feature of Atlas Search that allows you to search for documents based on their similarity to a given vector. This is particularly useful for applications like recommendation systems, where you want to find items similar to a user's preferences, or AI applications that require similarity-based searches for Retrival Augmented Generation capabilities.

First lets copy the following dataset into the Atlas Search Playground "Data Source" panel:

Place the following index under INDEX tab:

{
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": true,
    "fields": {
      "embedding": {
        "dimensions": 256,
        "similarity": "cosine",
        "type": "knnVector"
      }
    }
  }
}

Now lets create a vector search query:

This component allows you to generate OpenAI embeddings using your API key with 256 dimensional embedding vector.

OpenAI Embedding Generator

Generate 256-dimensional embeddings using OpenAI's API

If you don't have an OpenAI API key, you can use the following query.
